## B. Architecture / swappability

4. [open] Two divergent AttestationStore definitions:
   - Rust  qntx-core/src/storage/traits.rs — plain CRUD (put/get/delete/
     update/ids/clear) + QueryStore.
   - Go    ats/store.go — signing-aware (CreateAttestation,
     CreateAttestationInbound, GenerateAndCreateAttestation, bounded
     variants).
   "Swap out ats" is blocked because the swappable thing implements the
   Rust trait, but production runs the Go contract. Reconciling these into
   one seam is the actual prerequisite for swappability.

5. [open] qntx-core/src/storage/memory.rs (MemoryStore) — complete against
   the Rust trait, ~250 lines, zero deps, 8 tests. It is NOT a production-
   faithful backend: production goes Go contract -> ffi.rs -> SqliteStore
   (enforcement, distillation, signing, vec search). query() returns
   conflicts: Vec::new() // TODO. Keep it trivial (its value is being a
   cheap forcing function); do NOT replace it with an off-the-shelf
   in-memory DB. Note: SQLite ":memory:" already provides a production-
   faithful in-memory option with zero new dependencies.

6. [open] ats/storage/embedding_store.go (1,338 lines) — embedding storage
   baked into the attestation core. ADR-017 declares embedding a
   plugin-provided service. Same shape as the graph package, which was
   removed today (ADR-021). Candidate to follow graph out of core.

